---
import ArticleLayout from "../../components/ArticleLayout.astro";

const title = "Superposition (Like a Coin Mid-Flip) — Science";
const updated = "Updated: 2026";
---

<ArticleLayout title={title}>
  <article class="page">
    <header>
      <div class="hero-top">
        <a class="back" href="/">← Back to Atlas</a>
        <span class="chip">PHYSICS</span>
      </div>
      <h1>Superposition (Like a Coin Mid-Flip)</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">A quantum object can be in multiple valid states until interaction forces one observed outcome.</p>
      <p class="subtitle">{updated}</p>
    </header>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Key ideas</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card"><h3>It is a state, not ignorance</h3><p>Superposition means the system is genuinely described by multiple amplitudes, not that we simply do not know.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Measurement changes the setup</h3><p>Observation couples the system to an environment, selecting one outcome and suppressing alternatives.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><h3>Interference is the signature</h3><p>When alternatives combine and cancel like waves, we see direct evidence of superposition.</p></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Mental model</h2>
      <div class="card">
        <ul>
        <li>Prepare a state with two possible outcomes.</li>
        <li>Let amplitudes evolve and interfere.</li>
        <li>Measure once and get a single result, but repeated trials reveal probability weights.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <div class="faq">
        <details><summary>Is superposition the same as “both things are true forever”?</summary><p>No. It persists only while coherence is protected. Interaction with the environment rapidly decoheres it.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Does consciousness collapse the wave function?</summary><p>Mainstream physics does not require consciousness; physical interaction is sufficient.</p></details>
        <details><summary>Why should non-physicists care?</summary><p>Because superposition powers technologies like quantum sensing and potentially quantum computing.</p></details>
      </div>
    </section>

    <nav class="footnav">
      <a class="btn" href="/science">← Science index</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/future">Explore Future →</a>
    </nav>
  </article>

</ArticleLayout>
